  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PA - Shelter and Livelihood Support in Gorkha</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1000 households will have safe, transitional shelters within 2 months and community members and local masons will have improved preparedness and resilence following the shelter construction skills gained. 

The livelihood recovery strategies promoted by the project will start by benefiting 1000 households, with other indirect beneficaries expected, within 6 months.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022; Construction of toilets as per the local needs identified by assessment
&#x2022; Testing of water at sources to ensure clean, hyegenic drinking water
&#x2022; Chlorination of drinking water if required and community training in water chlorination
&#x2022; Hygiene promotion at household and community level through awareness raising and skills training

&#x2022; Assessment, identification and registration of destroyed houses
&#x2022; Formation of a local committee with a gender balance to mobilise volunteers for transitional shelter construction and early recovery
&#x2022; Community and local mason training on construction techniques for full shelters and temporary shelters 
&#x2022; Provision of CGI Sheets, fixers and tool kits to construction 
&#x2022; Construction of shelters supervised by an engineer

&#x2022; Provision of cash for skilled labour or materials for shelter goods 
&#x2022; Communities provided with goods (kitchen sets, clothing) 
&#x2022; Communities supported with livelihoods recovery (seeds, tools, livestock, poultry)</narrative>
  </description>
